parameters.name: MET
parameters.description: Mission Elapsed Time at the end of the accumulation.

parameters.name: DATA_QUALITY
parameters.description:
Data quality flag, taking on values of 0 (good) and
   1 (bad).

parameters.name: FIPS_SCANTYPE
parameters.description:
Indicates the FIPS Scan Mode and particle type.
    Tables referenced here are one of the eight E/q stepping tables
    loaded into the instrument. See the EPPS CDR SIS for details.
    =0 Normal Scan Heavy Ion, =1 High Temp Scan Heavy Ion,
    =2 Burst Scan Heavy Ion, =3 Test Scan Heavy Ion,
    =4 Table 4 Heavy Ion, =5 Table 5 Heavy Ion,
    =6 Table 6 Heavy Ion, =7 Table 7 Heavy Ion,
    =8 Normal Scan Proton, =9 High Temp Scan Proton,
    =10 Burst Scan Proton, =11 Test Scan Proton, =12 Table 4 Proton,
    =13 Table 5 Proton, =14 Table 6 Proton, =15 Table 7 Proton.

parameters.name: PRIORITY_DECIMATION
parameters.description:
Prior to FSW7 this column records the priority level
   of the PHA data. 0 = High Priority, 1 = Medium priority, 2 = Low priority.
   After FSW7 this column records the proton hardware decimation level for
   proton PHAs or =99 for Heavy Ion PHAs.

parameters.name: STEP_NUM
parameters.description:
E/q Step Number at which particle was measured.
   Value may range 0-63.

parameters.name: ENERGY_PER_CHARGE
parameters.description:
E/q value corresponding to step number at which
   particle was measured.

parameters.name: X
parameters.description:
In FSW4, FSW5, and FSW7, X is computed as
   [128*(w+(w-z)/5)/sum], and in FSW6, X is computed as
   [ 96*(s+(s-z)/5)/sum] where
	w = wedge - wedge_offset
	s = strip - strip_offset
	z = 14*(zigzag - zigzag_offset)/10
      sum = w+s+z.
   A value of -9999 means X is N/A.

parameters.name: Y
parameters.description:
In FSW4, FSW5, and FSW7, Y is computed as
   [128*(s+(s-z)/5)/sum], and in FSW6, Y is computed as
   [100*(s+2*(s-z)/11)/sum] where
	w = wedge - wedge_offset
	s = strip - strip_offset
	z = 14*(zigzag-zigzag_offset)/10
      sum = w+s+z.
   A value of -9999 means Y is N/A.

parameters.name: ZENITH_ANGLE
parameters.description:
Incident zenith angle for particle. A value of -9999
   means ZENITH_ANGLE cannot be properly calculated.

parameters.name: AZIMUTHAL_ANGLE
parameters.description:
Incident azimuthal angle for particle. A value of -9999
   means AZIMUTHAL_ANGLE cannot be properly calculated.

parameters.name: TIME_OF_FLIGHT
parameters.description: Time of flight in digital channels.

parameters.name: WEDGE
parameters.description: Wedge number. A value of -9999 means WEDGE is N/A.

parameters.name: STRIP
parameters.description: Strip number. A value of -9999 means STRIP is N/A.

parameters.name: ZIGZAG
parameters.description: Zigzag number. A value of -9999 means ZIGZAG is N/A.

parameters.name: MASS_PER_CHARGE
parameters.description: Estimated mass per charge (m/q) for particle.

parameters.name: WEIGHT
parameters.description:
Weight for particle, includes instrument-related
   factors such as efficiency and angle dependence.
